 :tx/rationale "Set t-f843f44c title=C8-FIX-5: M(t) spec-lang component penalizes external spec formats. The methodology score M(t) has a spec-lang component that checks for :spec/* entities in the store. External projects using different spec formats (e.g., plain markdown, YAML, Jira tickets) get penalized because they don't have :spec/* datoms. VIOLATES C8: M(t) should measure methodology adherence generically, not assume DDIS spec format. FIX: (1) In compute_methodology_score (guidance.rs), the spec-lang check currently requires :spec/type datoms. Make it configurable via policy: if policy defines spec attributes, use those. If no policy, fall back to checking for any structured claim entities (observations, decisions, tasks — not just :spec/*). (2) Alternative: make spec-lang score 1.0 (pass) when the store has no policy-defined spec format, rather than penalizing. (3) The key insight: methodology measures PROCESS, not FORMAT. A project that observes and harvests but uses markdown specs is still methodological. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Braid project (has :spec/* datoms): spec-lang component works as before. (B) External Go project (no :spec/* but has observations and tasks): spec-lang = 1.0 (not penalized). (C) Empty store: spec-lang = 0.0 (no methodology at all). (D) M(t) does not decrease when switching from braid to external project. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs (compute_methodology_score)"
